00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,060
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:00:05,060 --> 00:00:07,500
[Kim Insung]

3
00:00:09,940 --> 00:00:11,900
[Baek Zuho]

4
00:00:38,180 --> 00:00:42,460
[Star Struck]

5
00:00:47,540 --> 00:00:53,140
[Beer & Soju Bar]
[Vegetable hangover soup, Noodles in red bean paste]

6
00:00:57,820 --> 00:01:01,860
[hangover soup, noodles in red bean paste]

7
00:01:02,200 --> 00:01:03,280
Hello, sir.

8
00:01:03,280 --> 00:01:07,480
Do you know someone named Go Eunha who works here?

9
00:01:07,480 --> 00:01:08,770
Who?

10
00:01:09,760 --> 00:01:12,470
Oh, that skinny auntie?

11
00:01:12,470 --> 00:01:16,550
Yes, that's right. She's my mother.

12
00:01:16,550 --> 00:01:19,690
Can I see her now?

13
00:01:19,690 --> 00:01:23,380
She took a week off to visit her son.

14
00:01:25,480 --> 00:01:28,180
She must have several sons.

15
00:01:29,560 --> 00:01:31,810
No, I'm her only son.

16
00:01:33,039 --> 00:01:36,289
No wonder. I knew something was up.

17
00:01:36,289 --> 00:01:38,229
What do you mean?

18
00:01:39,340 --> 00:01:43,350
I knew something was up when creditors came to look for her every now and then.

19
00:01:43,350 --> 00:01:45,430
Creditors?

20
00:01:45,430 --> 00:01:49,320
Can you be more detailed? I can't even reach her now.

21
00:01:49,320 --> 00:01:50,729
Of course you can't reach her now.

22
00:01:50,729 --> 00:01:54,310
Why would a debtor who ran away with the money pick up her phone?

23
00:01:54,310 --> 00:01:56,830
My mom isn't that kind of person.

24
00:01:56,830 --> 00:01:59,289
You think so?

25
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:03,270
Do you know how much trouble she had caused?

26
00:02:05,020 --> 00:02:08,800
Just recently, she spilled noodles onto a customer's pants

27
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:11,490
and hasn't even paid the settlement fee yet.

28
00:02:11,490 --> 00:02:13,960
What a troublemaker.

29
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:16,340
Should I just call the police?

30
00:02:16,340 --> 00:02:18,040
How much is it?

31
00:02:18,040 --> 00:02:19,060
What?

32
00:02:19,060 --> 00:02:22,540
How much is that settlement fee?

33
00:02:22,540 --> 00:02:25,180
Tell me and I'll pay for it!

34
00:02:30,460 --> 00:02:34,020
[Noodles in red bean paste]

35
00:02:38,050 --> 00:02:40,910
Hey, kid!

36
00:02:42,570 --> 00:02:45,690
You look just like your photos.

37
00:02:45,690 --> 00:02:48,760
Eunha always bragged about her son to me.

38
00:02:48,760 --> 00:02:50,829
Do you know my mom?

39
00:02:53,130 --> 00:02:56,730
She didn't run away...

40
00:02:56,730 --> 00:02:59,310
She seems to be sick.

41
00:02:59,310 --> 00:03:02,960
She's hospitalized for an upcoming surgery.

42
00:03:05,630 --> 00:03:06,830
What?

43
00:03:13,020 --> 00:03:15,740
Sir, please hurry to Seonjae Central Hospital!

44
00:03:48,220 --> 00:03:52,579
[Come here quickly! Let's eat something delicious!]

45
00:04:23,100 --> 00:04:25,170
Excuse me.

46
00:04:25,170 --> 00:04:29,080
I'm sorry, but we close at 9 p.m..

47
00:04:30,750 --> 00:04:34,230
Also, you have to order something since you made a reservation.

48
00:04:34,230 --> 00:04:37,880
-Even if your guest is not coming...
-He'll be here.

49
00:04:39,670 --> 00:04:41,640
I'll order now.

50
00:05:00,780 --> 00:05:03,250
That darn Seo Hanjoon.

51
00:05:19,380 --> 00:05:21,580
[Seonjae Central Hospital]

52
00:05:23,670 --> 00:05:25,040
Where are the inpatient rooms?

53
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:27,500
Head left and go to the second floor.

54
00:05:49,409 --> 00:05:50,840
Mom.

55
00:05:56,200 --> 00:06:01,780
Gosh, why are you here?

56
00:06:20,390 --> 00:06:21,750
Whatever it was,

57
00:06:25,450 --> 00:06:28,320
you should've told me.

58
00:06:28,320 --> 00:06:30,880
I didn't even know you moved out.

59
00:06:35,260 --> 00:06:36,990
I'm sorry.

60
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:45,520
Don't cry.

61
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:48,210
I didn't tell you because I didn't want you to worry.

62
00:06:52,930 --> 00:06:58,250
By the way, my son is so handsome today.

63
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:04,990
What time is it now?

64
00:07:05,860 --> 00:07:08,990
Almost 10 p.m.?

65
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:12,950
Where's my jacket...

66
00:07:14,490 --> 00:07:15,950
and my phone...

67
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:36,800
It doesn't seem like you dressed up like this just to visit me.

68
00:07:37,850 --> 00:07:40,030
I guess you have an important appointment.

69
00:07:41,140 --> 00:07:44,440
It's still not too late. You should go now.

70
00:07:44,440 --> 00:07:47,040
It's too late.

71
00:07:47,040 --> 00:07:49,159
You never know.

72
00:07:49,159 --> 00:07:50,550
Hanjoon.

73
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:58,740
Don't give up on what you like easily.

74
00:08:07,930 --> 00:08:11,650
My son must have spent a lot to come all the way here.

75
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:24,940
Hurry and go.

76
00:08:42,010 --> 00:08:43,429
Let's date.

77
00:08:47,830 --> 00:08:52,060
But... I have one condition.

78
00:08:53,880 --> 00:08:55,230
A condition?

79
00:08:56,610 --> 00:08:58,760
Don't cut off contact.

80
00:09:00,190 --> 00:09:05,450
If you refuse to respond to your calls and texts... if that happens again...

81
00:09:08,560 --> 00:09:10,240
I'll never see you ever again.

82
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:14,480
Promise me.

83
00:09:16,620 --> 00:09:19,660
Okay, I promise you.

84
00:09:19,660 --> 00:09:21,330
I won't do that again.

85
00:09:47,980 --> 00:09:49,860
[Exit]

86
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:37,530
Have you been crying?

87
00:10:37,530 --> 00:10:39,710
Because you were afraid you won't get to see me anymore?

88
00:10:43,940 --> 00:10:46,830
Well...

89
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:55,020
What's wrong? What happened to your lips?

90
00:10:55,020 --> 00:10:56,390
Did you get hit?

91
00:10:58,290 --> 00:10:59,510
No.

92
00:11:00,710 --> 00:11:04,890
My parents were fighting over the studio apartment's deposit,

93
00:11:04,890 --> 00:11:07,100
so I just told them to take it. And now...

94
00:11:10,930 --> 00:11:13,160
Where do I live now?

95
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:17,430
Damn it, screw everything!

96
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:20,710
What?

97
00:11:20,710 --> 00:11:25,560
Hey, don't worry! You have me!

98
00:11:26,660 --> 00:11:28,540
You punk.

99
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:32,760
Focus on responding to my calls and texts first.

100
00:11:36,150 --> 00:11:37,900
I'm sorry.

101
00:11:37,900 --> 00:11:41,780
Right, I have something for you.

102
00:11:43,470 --> 00:11:44,760
It's here.

103
00:11:57,910 --> 00:12:00,860
How did you know my lips would be chapped and prepared this?

104
00:12:01,940 --> 00:12:03,340
Apply it now.

105
00:12:04,830 --> 00:12:06,170
Apply it for me.

106
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:39,840
Don't you want to know what gift I've prepared for you?

107
00:12:42,150 --> 00:12:43,590
You also prepared something?

108
00:12:43,590 --> 00:12:44,860
What is it?

109
00:12:46,520 --> 00:12:47,970
A couple ring.

110
00:12:50,190 --> 00:12:51,800
A couple ring?

111
00:13:02,820 --> 00:13:05,640
Two hours will be more than enough time.

112
00:13:05,640 --> 00:13:07,490
Pick your favorite design,

113
00:13:07,490 --> 00:13:10,060
and measure the circumference of your fingers.

114
00:13:10,060 --> 00:13:12,890
I can also make engravings inside if you like.

115
00:13:14,430 --> 00:13:16,310
Engravings?

116
00:13:16,310 --> 00:13:19,640
If you engrave your initials or anniversary dates,

117
00:13:19,640 --> 00:13:21,480
it would be meaningful and nice.

118
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:29,240
Then, I'll come back again with my friend on that day.

119
00:13:29,240 --> 00:13:30,440
Is that okay?

120
00:13:30,440 --> 00:13:31,730
Of course.

121
00:13:31,730 --> 00:13:35,640
But you have to come by 9 p.m. at the latest.

122
00:13:35,640 --> 00:13:37,800
Okay, that's enough time.

123
00:13:38,730 --> 00:13:40,490
Okay, take your time to browse then.

124
00:13:48,730 --> 00:13:54,680
Oh... I... ruined your plan, didn't I?

125
00:13:55,440 --> 00:13:56,720
I'm sorry.

126
00:13:58,920 --> 00:14:00,620
Not yet.

127
00:14:01,840 --> 00:14:03,030
Huh?

128
00:14:04,440 --> 00:14:05,970
Give me your hand.

129
00:14:28,340 --> 00:14:29,890
Isn't it well-made?

130
00:15:51,100 --> 00:15:56,140
[Star Struck]
